Comment.value: Init dialog with PC when PC crosses trigger A on design doc

value.0: If we are to survive the wailing death, Neverwinter has need of men and women like you.
Go ahead, my friend. I will answer them as best I may.
Is there anything else you need, <FirstName>?
Aribeth and I are of one heart and soul, it is true. But that does not make her any less a paragon of virtue. None who serve Neverwinter are more capable than my Lady Aribeth.
My Lady Aribeth is in her office at Castle Never. There she works tirelessly to put an end to the plague that ravages Neverwinter.
I do what I can to ease the suffering of those within Castle Never who have been infected with the Wailing Death, although they are beyond my power to save.
I do what we can to comfort these poor souls, but we can do little else. Not even Neverwinter's most powerful priests can heal or raise those who contract the Wailing Death.
No one yet knows how the plague spreads, though contact with the infected does not seem to be a catalyst. Even so, people are burning the bodies and locking themselves indoors just to be safe.
People are scared. They're on the verge of panic and even open rebellion, and the city watch struggles to keep order.

Unfortunately not, my friend. I must save all the coffers, donations, and gold I make from these supplies for those who need it most. However, I hear Olgerd in the Docks district will buy any sort of item. Was there something else you needed?
I am sorry, but that is beyond my skills. Eltoora will happily identify your items for a fee - find her in the Cloaktower outside here.
Of course. Hold still, my friend.
I don't have any more questions.
Can I sell something to you?
I need to purchase some priestly supplies.
